5 3. HEART DISEASE; OR
6 4. A CARDIOMETABOLIC DISEASE.
7 (3) “HEALTH CARE PROVIDER” MEANS:
8 (I) A PERSON WHO IS LICENSED, CERTIFIED, OR OTHERWISE
9 AUTHORIZED UNDER THE HEALTH OCCUPATIONS ARTICLE TO PROVIDE HEALTH
10 CARE IN THE ORDINARY COURSE OF BUSINESS OR PRACTICE OF A PROFESSION, OR
11 IN AN APPROVED EDUCATION OR TRAINING PROGRAM; OR
12 (II) A COMMUNITY HEALTH WORKER CERTIFIED UNDER TITLE
13 13, SUBTITLE 37 OF THIS ARTICLE.
14 (B) THE PROGRAM SHALL PROVIDE COVERAGE FOR SELF–MEASURED
15 BLOOD PRESSURE MONITORING FOR ALL ELIGIBLE PROGRAM RECIPIENTS,
16 INCLUDING:
17 (1) THE PROVISION OF VALIDATED HOME BLOOD PRESSURE
18 MONITORS; AND
19 (2) REIMBURSEMENT OF HEALTH CARE PROVIDER AND OTHER STAFF
20 TIME USED FOR PATIENT TRAINING, TRANSMISSION OF BLOOD PRESSURE DATA,
21 INTERPRETATION OF BLOOD PRESSURE READINGS AND REPORTING, REMOTE
22 PATIENT MONITORING, AND THE DELIVERY OF CO–INTERVENTIONS, INCLUDING
23 EDUCATIONAL MATERIALS OR CLASSES.
24 (C) THE PROGRAM SHALL DEVELOP AND IMPLEMENT AN EDUCATION
25 CAMPAIGN TO INFORM ELIGIBLE PROGRAM RECIPIENTS AND HEALTH CARE
26 PROVIDERS ABOUT THE BENEFITS AND USAGE OF BLOOD PRESSURE MONITORING
27 TECHNOLOGY AND THE AVAILABILITY OF ASSISTANCE WITH SETUP AND
28 TROUBLESHOOTING.
29 (D) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1 EACH YEAR, BEGINNING IN 2027, THE
30 DEPARTMENT SHALL SUBMIT A REPORT TO THE SENATE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND

